{"key":"post-6841038","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6841038</id>\n<content>Bury it into a manure or compost pile in your backyard and it will fruit there.  You're more likely to get molds indoors because it was far from sterile.  That's how I grew my first mushroom crop ever back in 1971, which got me started.  That was before there was any books, kits or anything, and of course, no internet.  I brought home a cow patty from a field in east texas to where I lived at the time in Dallas, and stuck it into some compost.  That compost pile produced hundreds of mushrooms that whole year.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14441203</next>\n<prev>6840727</prev>\n<first>6840727</first>\n<last>14443724</last>\n<when>1177696720</when>\n<utime>04/27/07 08:58 PM</utime>\n</post>"}